# id: GoogleCloudStorageRepository -> static <T> T getSetting(Setting<T> setting, RepositoryMetaData metadata)
commentText: Get a given setting from the repository settings, throwing a {@link RepositoryException} if the setting does not exist or is empty.
codeText: static <T> T getSetting(Setting<T> setting, RepositoryMetaData metadata) {_        T value = setting.get(metadata.settings())__        if (value == null) {_            throw new RepositoryException(metadata.name(), "Setting [" + setting.getKey() + "] is not defined for repository")__        }_        if ((value instanceof String) && (Strings.hasText((String) value)) == false) {_            throw new RepositoryException(metadata.name(), "Setting [" + setting.getKey() + "] is empty for repository")__        }_        return value__    }
